<!-- omikuji_app/app/views/pages/architecture.html.erb -->

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto py-24 px-6 font-sans text-stone-800">
  <header class="text-center mb-24 animate-slide-up">
    <div class="inline-block bg-stone-900 text-white px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-8">
      <span class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-[0.3em]">Full Stack AI Implementation</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-7xl font-serif font-black mb-6 tracking-tighter text-stone-900">System Architecture</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-stone-500 font-serif italic max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Bypassing the cloud. A technical breakdown of high-performance deep learning inference running natively in Ruby on Rails.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-32">
    <!-- Layer 1: Analysis -->
    <div class="bg-stone-900 text-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-2xl hover:-translate-y-2 transition-all duration-500 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.1s">
      <div class="bg-red-800 w-12 h-12 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-8 shadow-lg shadow-red-900/40">
        <span class="text-2xl">👂</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic">The Ear</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">
        <strong>BERT Analysis</strong><br>
        Fine-tuned <code>bert-base-japanese-v3</code> model localized to the Ruby process.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3 pt-6 border-t border-white/10">
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-500">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-red-600 rounded-full mr-2"></div> MeCab Integration
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-500">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-red-600 rounded-full mr-2"></div> WordPiece Tokenizer
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 2: Generation -->
    <div class="bg-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-2 transition-all duration-500 border border-stone-100 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.2s">
      <div class="bg-stone-100 w-12 h-12 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-8">
        <span class="text-2xl">🗣️</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic text-stone-900">The Voice</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">
        <strong>GPT-2 Generative</strong><br>
        <code>rinna/japanese-gpt2-small</code> performing real-time autoregressive text completion.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3 pt-6 border-t border-stone-100">
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-stone-900 rounded-full mr-2"></div> Nucleus Sampling
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-stone-900 rounded-full mr-2"></div> Repetition Penalty
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 3: Delivery -->
    <div class="bg-stone-900 text-white p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-2xl hover:-translate-y-2 transition-all duration-500 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.3s">
      <div class="bg-red-800 w-12 h-12 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-8 shadow-lg shadow-red-900/40">
        <span class="text-2xl">⛩️</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic">The Shrine</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">
        <strong>Rails Monolith</strong><br>
        Coordinating state, persistence, and inference without external API overhead.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3 pt-6 border-t border-white/10">
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-500">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-red-600 rounded-full mr-2"></div> Turbo Streams
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-500">
          <div class="w-1 h-1 bg-red-600 rounded-full mr-2"></div> Stimulus FX
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-20">
    <div class="relative pl-12 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.4s">
       <div class="absolute left-0 top-2 w-0.5 h-full bg-gradient-to-b from-red-800 to-transparent"></div>
       <div class="absolute left-[-4px] top-2 w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-red-800 rounded-full shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(153,27,27,0.5)]"></div>
       <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic">01. Local Tokenization</h2>
       <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">Unlike English, Japanese has no spaces. We interface directly with the system's <code>MeCab</code> analyzer via the <code>natto</code> gem to perform morphological segmentation before passing tokens to our local <code>WordPiece</code> and <code>SentencePiece</code> encoders.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="relative pl-12 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.5s">
       <div class="absolute left-0 top-2 w-0.5 h-full bg-gradient-to-b from-stone-900 to-transparent"></div>
       <div class="absolute left-[-4px] top-2 w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-stone-900 rounded-full"></div>
       <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic">02. The ONNX Engine</h2>
       <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">The <code>onnxruntime</code> gem allows Ruby to execute pre-trained Python models at C++ speeds. We load both the BERT and GPT-2 weights into a thread-safe singleton, ensuring sub-second inference latency for real-time user interaction.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="relative pl-12 animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.6s">
       <div class="absolute left-0 top-2 w-0.5 h-8 bg-stone-200"></div>
       <div class="absolute left-[-4px] top-2 w-2.5 h-2.5 bg-stone-200 rounded-full"></div>
       <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 italic">03. Deterministic Decoding</h2>
       <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">To ensure high-quality fortunes from a small LLM, we implemented a custom <code>Nucleus (Top-P)</code> sampling algorithm in Ruby. By penalizing repetitive tokens and strictly controlling the temperature, the model delivers varied yet coherent mystical insights.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="mt-32 text-center animate-slide-up" style="animation-delay: 0.8s">
    <%= link_to root_path, class: "group inline-flex items-center space-x-4 bg-red-800 text-white px-10 py-5 rounded-full hover:bg-stone-900 transition-all shadow-2xl hover:shadow-stone-900/30 active:scale-95" do %>
      <span class="text-sm font-black uppercase tracking-[0.2em]">Return to the Shrine</span>
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-red-400" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18" />
      </svg>
    <% end %>
  </footer>
</div>
